'''Kagoshima Shrine''' (鹿児島神社, ''Kagoshima Jinja'') is a Shinto shrine located in Minamimatsubara-chō, {{ill|Tarumizu City|ja|垂水市|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, Kagoshima Prefecture. It is also known as '''Shimomiya Shrine'''. Under the {{ill|Modern system of Ranked Shinto shrines|ja|近代社格制度|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, it was classified as a Village Shrine.
== Enshrined Deities == *{{ill|Hoori|ja|ホオリ|lt=Hikohodemi-no-Mikoto|lt_ja=彦火火出見尊|qq=draft|qq=draft}} *{{ill|Toyotama-hime|ja|トヨタマヒメ|lt=Toyotamahime-no-Mikoto|lt_ja=豊玉姫尊|qq=draft|qq=draft}} *{{ill|Tamayoribime|ja|タマヨリビメ (日向神話)|1=Tamayori-hime (mother of Jimmu)|lt=Tamayori-hime|lt=Tamayoribime-no-Mikoto|lt_ja=玉依姫尊|qq=draft|qq=draft}} *{{ill|Sarutahiko|ja|サルタヒコ|lt=Shioshiji-no-Okina, Sarutahiko-no-Mikoto|lt_ja=塩司翁・猿田彦命|qq=draft|qq=draft}} *{{ill|Emperor Tenji|ja|天智天皇|qq=draft|qq=draft}} *Ōmiya-hime (traditionally said to be one of Emperor Tenji's consorts)
== History == The shrine is traditionally said to have been founded in the late {{ill|Nara period|ja|奈良時代|qq=draft|qq=draft}}. There are two theories regarding its establishment: one suggests it was transferred from {{ill|Hirakiki Shrine|ja|枚聞神社|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, while another posits that it was established in the sacred territory of {{ill|Kagoshima Jingū|ja|鹿児島神宮|qq=draft|qq=draft}}.
Although its precise founding date is unknown, it has strong historical ties to {{ill|Kagoshima Jingū|ja|鹿児島神宮|qq=draft|qq=draft}} and {{ill|Kagoshima Shrine (Kagoshima City)|ja|鹿児島神社 (鹿児島市)|qq=draft|qq=draft}}. The shrine is thought to have originally worshipped {{ill|Sakurajima|ja|桜島|qq=draft|qq=draft}} as its {{ill|shintai|ja|神体|1=Shintai|qq=draft|qq=draft}}. Additionally, it maintains a strong connection to {{ill|Tekan Shrine|ja|手貫神社|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, another shrine in Tarumizu City known locally as "Kamimiya Shrine."
